      <hedline>
        <hl1>LITTLE BIG PEOPLE</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Too many youngsters are being raised by surrogate parents like nannies, baby sitters and housekeepers, while, in the more deprived homes of the city, day-care personnel, grandmothers, aunts, brothers and sisters have to provide for the emotional and social needs of children. Family life involving parenting by parents is absent from too many homes. STANLEY SEIDMAN New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
